Utilities¶

In [41]:
# 14 keypoint format to encode the skeleton
LIMBS14=[
    [0,1],[1,2],[3,4],[4,5],[2,3],[6,7],[7,8],[9,10],[10,11],[2,8],[3,9],[8,12],[9,12],[12,13]
]

# 17 keypoint format to encode the skeleton
LIMBS17 = [[0, 1], [0, 2], [1, 2], [1, 3], [2, 4], [3, 5], [4, 6], [5, 7], [7, 9], [6, 8], [8, 10], [5, 11], [11, 13], [13, 15],
        [6, 12], [12, 14], [14, 16], [5, 6], [11, 12]]

def line_3d(pose):
    segments = []
    for limb in LIMBS17:
        segments.append([pose[limb[0]].tolist(), pose[limb[1]].tolist()])
    return segments

def add_limbs_on(plt,joint):
    np.random.seed(42)
    for k in LIMBS14:
        x = [float(joint[k[0], 0]), float(joint[k[1], 0])]
        y = [float(joint[k[0], 1]), float(joint[k[1], 1])]
        plt.plot(x, y, c='r', lw=1.5, marker='o', markerfacecolor='w', markersize=2, markeredgewidth=1)

gpus = [int(i) for i in config.GPUS.split(',')]
print('=> Loading data ..')
normalize = transforms.Normalize(
    mean=[0.485, 0.456, 0.406], std=[0.229, 0.224, 0.225])

test_dataset = eval('dataset.' + config.DATASET.TEST_DATASET)(
    config, config.DATASET.TEST_SUBSET, False,
    transforms.Compose([
        transforms.ToTensor(),
        normalize,
    ]))

test_loader = torch.utils.data.DataLoader(
    test_dataset,
    batch_size=config.TEST.BATCH_SIZE * len(gpus),
    shuffle=False,
    num_workers=config.WORKERS,
    pin_memory=True)


ds_Chico = Chico( #eval('dataset.' + config.DATASET.TRAIN_DATASET)( # dataset.shelf()
    config, config.DATASET.TEST_SUBSET, False,
    transforms.Compose([
        transforms.ToTensor(),
        normalize,
    ]))


print('=> Constructing models ..')
model = eval('models.' + config.MODEL + '.get_multi_person_pose_net')(
    config, is_train=True)
with torch.no_grad():
    model = torch.nn.DataParallel(model, device_ids=gpus).cuda()

test_model_file=r"../output/chico_synthetic/multi_person_posenet_50/prn64_cpn80x80x20/model_best.pth.tar"

if config.TEST.MODEL_FILE and os.path.isfile(test_model_file):
    model.module.load_state_dict(torch.load(test_model_file))
else:
    raise ValueError('Check the model file for testing!')
